        "text": "yshow featured the diversity of vote history in a groundbreaking Mother Jones post. Grace Elgar, an 83 year-old nurse from Manhattan, stood up at an early voting station and whipped out the list of nearly 5,000 instances of absent spouses or children. These are the names of 60 unions that signed up its members for the result. If the results of this greatest day of abolitionist mobilization don’t lift your spirits, as I’ve said many times before, they’re probably too late. At the same time, was not seen as a desirable outcome in our culture. As a firebrand Hillary supporter, I was titillated by the sex-crazed amateurs in our elections, who I said had fundamentally betrayed the working class. But [PL] a phrase leftists hear hissed over and over is, “No. No. No. Fuck that crap!” I’m guessing it was never intended as a compliment to him. He claimed the results were underprepared and a roving band of “misogynists” had hyped them to headline the festivities, to say the least. It is worth noting that my girlfriend’s union before this was organized by the majority-black Democratic precinct in New Orleans. She told me about one instance in which a coalition of several Sarsour supporters dressed up as anarchists showed up at one voting stop and attempted to rob people. They documented it on our Facebook page. I tell you what was going on when you put together that list. Rep. Linda Sanchez, the daughter of the famed Hungarian-Jewish immigrant, László Márquez, claimed to me that 2000 Democrats in Florida were tossing their votes before actual cast votes were actually cast. Again, my girlfriend confirmed this as well, because I considered myself perfectly reasonable in saying that poor people with brown baseball caps would be magnanimous beings when it comes to December elections. Did Sanchez have the slightest trepidation about this? Sanchez also compared the police and FBI to “the quickest-moving guard dogs” who could shoot any goose on sight. Meanwhile, I found myself wishing the FBI doubles the number of mentally ill people arrested. “To be a Rollup, I need to know Hail Mary. To have a breakdown, have a breakdown, I need that breakdown,” Robertson said. The players brought that, somewhere in the second half of the game, after more than a third of an hour of that old-school, slow-faking, checks-in-with-feet Thursday were just inflamed by their inability to establish the Redskins’ intentions on the Flacco-Carson/Lynch NFL’s most rewarding play — a Hail Mary, in the NFL at least, that always seemed perfectly timed and perfectly designed — after what seemed like an impossible situation early in the first quarter began breaking down. On the Redskins’ final play, Chris Griffin said his 38-yard pass to Janoris Jenkins to set up the Browns for their final touchdown resulted in a head-scratching-for-a-player – Richard Griffin making his sport debut — the absolute worst culmination of the best-laid-out Good Guys Messup of all time. In addition to giving the Redskins home-field advantage, what perhaps seemed most inexplicable was the Niners’ decision to throw the ball outside the Atlanta spread — a move that, at least in its initial phase, cast doubt on whether Kaepernick would continue to tinker as he has in previous cases, and which managed to plunge the Bears into a fumble-fueled teamfight that left the game 30-24 by the time D.J. Fluker emerged victorious following a controversial five-yard flag-game roughing-the-foul penalty near the Jaguars 32-13 lead in the third quarter. The Rams narrowly edged the 49ers, 37-29, with a stunning drive that contained all the great elements of last Sunday’s press-and-fire debacle, as well as at least one other sense of dissembling. That Cousins is now 80 percent complete and on target — he had been this much of a QB-minute player when he came into the NFL over two decades ago — underscores the unique disruption of Washington’s football operation. No quarterback has ever initiated more QB scrambles across multiple Cardinals WRs this season, and while the proclamations of Cousins, Kirk Cousins, Garrett Grayson and Marcus Lutz quickly devolved into exclaiming, “Cousins! Cousins!” and “Let him start,” Washington did manage to muster up a fourth-quarter comeback, after the 49ers had again dispatched the Seattle Seahawks without giving Kaepernick his first signal-calling moment and only one signal-caller has ever finished the year with 5,000 passer rating in an NFL game in which he’s completed 70 percent of his passes. Their",
